{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 20:19:09.703520", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary of observed behavior\n- Fabric control-plane health: All EBGP adjacencies between leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established and exchanging prefixes. No flaps observed; Up/Down timers ~1 minute and counting. Each leaf originates its /24 and spines/super-spine learn them as expected.\n- Data-plane anomaly: End-to-end reachability involving host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24) is broken. Most other host-to-host paths are healthy.\n\nReachability tests and symptoms\n- From the lab-wide reachability probe:\n  - Many pairs succeed with 0% loss and low RTTs.\n  - Paths involving pc_0_0 consistently time out:\n    - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: timed out\n    - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: timed out\n    - pc_1_0 → pc_0_0: timed out\n- Direct gateway checks:\n  - pc_0_0 → 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0 SVI): timed out.\n  - pc_0_1 ↔ 10.0.1.1 (leaf_router_0_1 SVI): OK (0% loss, <1 ms).\n- Leaf-router initiated tests:\n  - leaf_router_0_0 → 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0): fails with “ping: connect: Invalid argument”.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 ↔ 10.0.1.2 (pc_0_1): OK.\n\nHost and router interface status\n- pc_0_0:\n  - eth0: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 (correct for its subnet).\n  - ARP for 10.0.0.1 present: 10.0.0.1 lladdr ae:d9:b1:a2:2d:af state DELAY.\n- leaf_router_0_0:\n  - eth4: 10.0.0.1/24 up (local SVI toward pc_0_0 subnet).\n  - ARP has entry for 10.0.0.2: lladdr a6:7d:3d:51:f4:8e state STALE (indicates L2 is OK and was resolved).\n- leaf_router_0_1:\n  - eth4: 10.0.1.1/24 up; ARP and reachability to 10.0.1.2 are normal.\n\nRouting tables and BGP state\n- leaf_router_0_0 (BGP summary):\n  - 4 EBGP peers (two spines in pod, etc.) all Established; PfxRcd counts sensible.\n  - BGP network statement present for 10.0.0.0/24.\n- leaf_router_0_0 (RIB/FIB):\n  - FRR “show ip route” shows both:\n    - K - kernel route: 10.0.0.0/24 unreachable (blackhole)\n    - C>* directly connected 10.0.0.0/24 via eth4\n  - Linux kernel route table (ip route): only shows\n    - blackhole 10.0.0.0/24\n    - …and NO “10.0.0.0/24 dev eth4” connected route in the FIB\n  - Route lookup test:\n    - “ip -4 route get 10.0.0.2” returns “RTNETLINK answers: Invalid argument” (consistent with a blackhole being selected for that destination).\n  - Result: The kernel is preferring the blackhole for 10.0.0.0/24, overshadowing the connected route to eth4.\n- leaf_router_0_1 (RIB/FIB):\n  - Normal: 10.0.1.0/24 dev eth4 scope link present; no blackhole route.\n\nFault localization\n- Faulty device: leaf_router_0_0.\n- Faulty function: IPv4 routing for the directly connected LAN 10.0.0.0/24 on eth4.\n- Blast radius: All traffic destined to or sourced from 10.0.0.0/24 that must be forwarded by leaf_router_0_0 is affected. This includes:\n  - Echo replies from 10.0.0.1 to pc_0_0 (router receives ICMP echo request to its local IP, but the reply to 10.0.0.2 is dropped due to the blackhole route).\n  - Any transit traffic toward 10.0.0.2/24 arriving from elsewhere in the fabric (dropped at leaf_router_0_0 due to blackhole).\n\nRoot cause\n- An erroneous blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/24 is installed in the kernel on leaf_router_0_0, overriding the connected route on eth4. This causes the router to drop all packets whose destination is within 10.0.0.0/24, effectively isolating pc_0_0 and any other hosts in that subnet.\n- Evidence:\n  - ip route on leaf_router_0_0 shows “blackhole 10.0.0.0/24” and no active connected route entry for the same prefix.\n  - FRR’s view shows the connected route exists, but the kernel has the blackhole selected in the FIB (confirmed by route-get failure and ping behavior).\n  - ARP adjacency exists on both sides, indicating L2 is functional; the drop is at L3 due to the blackhole.\n\nNetwork health assessment\n- Control-plane: Healthy (EBGP across all tiers is up and exchanging expected prefixes).\n- Data-plane: Healthy for all observed prefixes except 10.0.0.0/24. The only abnormal behavior is on leaf_router_0_0 where the blackhole route is present.\n- Impact: Loss of connectivity to/from pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) and any traffic to 10.0.0.0/24 through leaf_router_0_0. All other hosts/subnets appear to operate normally.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13506, "output_tokens": 5303, "total_tokens": 18809, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 13056}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3968}}}
